tool.name: CreateGRGFromPoint

param.name: input_start_location
param.dialogReference: Select a layer for the center point for the gridded reference graphic, or use the input_start_location to sketch a starting point on the map.

param.name: cell_units
param.expression: Meters | Feet | Miles | Kilometers | Nautical Miles | Yards
param.dialogReference:
The units of the Cell Width and Cell Height.

  • Meters

  • Feet

  • Kilometers

  • Miles

  • Nautical Miles

  • Yards

param.name: label_start_position
param.dialogReference:
The grid cell where the labeling will start from. The default is Upper-Left

  • Upper-Left

  • Lower-Left

  • Upper-Right

  • Lower-Right

param.name: label_type
param.dialogReference:
The labeling type for each grid cell. The default is Alpha-Numeric.

  • Alpha-Numeric: letter/number combination as A1, A2, A3, A4....X1, X2, X3...

  • Alpha-Alpha: letter/letter combination: AA, AB, AC, AD, ... XA, XB, XC...

  • Numeric: sequentially numbered 1, 2, 3, 4, .... 99, 100, 101...

param.name: label_seperator
param.dialogReference:
Seperator to be used between x and y values when using Alpha-Alpha labeling. Example: A-A, A-AA, AA-A.

  • -

  • ,

  • .

  • /

param.name: grid_angle
param.dialogReference: The angle to rotate the grid by. Valid values between -89 and 89.

param.name: output_grg_features
param.dialogReference: Specify the output grg features to be created.

tool.summary: Creates a Gridded Reference Graphic (GRG) over a specified area with a custom size. The grid is centered on the input start location. The cells are labeled with sequential letters or numbers.
tool.usage:
• The Grid (text) field in the Output GRG Features contains the cell labeling.

  • Output GRG Features are in Web Mercator coordinate system.
